"prompt_str": "<TO_OPTIMIZE kind="User">
Given this business email:
- Content: {email_content}
- Sender's Position: {management_position}
- Time: {time_sent}

Classify the dominant emotion into exactly ONE of these categories considering business context:
Joy: immediate happiness/achievement
Sadness: disappointment/negative outcomes
Anger: strong disapproval/hostility
Fear: concern about risks/negative possibilities
Surprise: unexpected events/discoveries
Disgust: strong disapproval/rejection
Trust: confidence in processes/reliability
Anticipation: future expectations/planning
Content: steady satisfaction/meeting standards
Frustration: blocked goals/difficulties

Analysis steps:
1. Identify key emotional language and temporal focus (present vs future)
2. Consider management context and professional tone
3. Apply these priority rules:
   - Choose emotions matching the primary message intent
   - For future-focused content
column8: prefer Anticipation over Joy\n   - For process/system updates
column9: favor Trust or Content\n   - For mixed emotions
column10: select the strongest/most dominant one\n\nOutput exactly ONE word from the emotion list above
